TY  - JOUR
T1  - Solution of Spatial Equilibrium Problems with Benders Decomposition
AU  - Polito, Joseph
AU  - McCarl, Bruce A.
AU  - Morin, Thomas L.
Y1  - 1980/06/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.26.6.593
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.26.6.593
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 593
EP  - 605
VL  - 26
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Spatial equilibrium problems are frequently formulated as large scale quadratic programming problems or linear complementarity problems. We show that these problems can be reduced to two or more smaller problems with Generalized Benders Decomposition. The procedure then becomes iterative with the repetitive solution of the smaller problems. In practice, the iterative procedure has converged rapidly.
AB  - Spatial equilibrium problems are frequently formulated as large scale quadratic programming problems or linear complementarity problems. We show that these problems can be reduced to two or more smaller problems with Generalized Benders Decomposition. The procedure then becomes iterative with the repetitive solution of the smaller problems. In practice, the iterative procedure has converged rapidly.
