TY  - JOUR
T1  - The Relationship between Attributes, Brand Preference, and Choice: A Stochastic View
AU  - Blin, Jean-Marie
AU  - Dodson, Joe A.
Y1  - 1980/06/01
PY  - 1980
DA  - 1980/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.26.6.606
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.26.6.606
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 606
EP  - 619
VL  - 26
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper draws from two separate research traditions in marketing theories of consumer behavior: multiattribute expectancy-value models and stochastic choice models. A behavioral basis for the observed brand-switching phenomenon is found in the multiattributed evaluation of alternatives and the uncertainty surrounding such evaluation. A model is proposed to deal with this phenomenon and is fitted against a comprehensive data set. The model is found to compare favorably in predictive value with other models.
AB  - This paper draws from two separate research traditions in marketing theories of consumer behavior: multiattribute expectancy-value models and stochastic choice models. A behavioral basis for the observed brand-switching phenomenon is found in the multiattributed evaluation of alternatives and the uncertainty surrounding such evaluation. A model is proposed to deal with this phenomenon and is fitted against a comprehensive data set. The model is found to compare favorably in predictive value with other models.
